**Root cause:** Every test follows the same template — call the method, optionally `IsNotNull` the result. This is the classic **"coverage-padding"** anti-pattern: the coverage tool sees every line executed, but zero behavioral contracts are enforced. The 95% coverage number is meaningless because **10 out of 10 tests would still pass if every method returned wrong results**.
